Supplementary 1. Description of the data

A. Distribution of ES

df_main$outlier_pre_post = ifelse(is_outlier(df_main$yi - df_main$yi_p), df_main$ID_out, NA_character_)
df_main$outlier = ifelse(is_outlier(df_main$yi), df_main$ID_out, NA_character_)
df_plot = df_main %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(yi, yi_p), names_to = "es_type", values_to = "smd") 
df_plot$es_type[df_plot$es_type=="yi"] <- "Pre-post SMD"
df_plot$es_type[df_plot$es_type=="yi_p"] <- "Post SMD"
df_plot$ID = rep(1:(nrow(df_plot)/2), each = 2)
ggplot(df_plot, aes(x = outcome, y = smd)) + 
  geom_violin(aes(fill = outcome, alpha = 0.3)) +
   geom_boxplot(width=0.1)+
  geom_jitter(aes(fill = outcome), binaxis='y', stackdir='center', dotsize=0.4, alpha = 0.2, position=position_jitter(0.05)) + 
  facet_grid(es_type ~ "") +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(y = "SMD value") +
  theme(text = element_text(size = 18),
        legend.position = "none",
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=20, face="bold"), 
        axis.title.x = element_text(size=20, face="bold")) +
  coord_flip()

Supplementary 2. Main analysis

A. Results

V.SCE  <- impute_covariance_matrix(vi = df_main$vi, 
                                   cluster = df_main$study_ID, 
                                   r = 0.8,
                                   return_list = FALSE,
                                   smooth_vi = TRUE,
                                   subgroup = df_main$outcome)

metafor.SCE <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                               mods =  ~ outcome - 1,
                               data = df_main,
                               random = ~ outcome | study_ID,
                               struct = "DIAG",
                               sparse = TRUE)

res.main = coef_sand(model = metafor.SCE, vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.main$outcome = gsub("outcome", "", res.main$outcome)
res.main[,2:ncol(res.main)] = round(res.main[,2:ncol(res.main)], 3)
res.main$Analysis = "Primary analysis"

kbl(res.main) %>%
  kable_classic()
outcome beta SE tstat df p_Satt CI_L CI_U Analysis
interoception 0.406 0.118 3.428 9.192 0.007 0.139 0.673 Primary analysis
symptoms 0.526 0.136 3.881 9.374 0.003 0.221 0.831 Primary analysis

Heterogeneity

metafor.SCE
## 
## Multivariate Meta-Analysis Model (k = 46; method: REML)
## 
## Variance Components:
## 
## outer factor: study_ID (nlvls = 12)
## inner factor: outcome  (nlvls = 2)
## 
##             estim    sqrt  k.lvl  fixed          level 
## tau^2.1    0.0900  0.3001     33     no  interoception 
## tau^2.2    0.1314  0.3625     13     no       symptoms 
## 
## Test for Residual Heterogeneity:
## QE(df = 44) = 406.7252, p-val < .0001
## 
## Test of Moderators (coefficients 1:2):
## QM(df = 2) = 26.8065, p-val < .0001
## 
## Model Results:
## 
##                       estimate      se    zval    pval   ci.lb   ci.ub 
## outcomeinteroception    0.4062  0.1179  3.4451  0.0006  0.1751  0.6372  *** 
## outcomesymptoms         0.5263  0.1362  3.8650  0.0001  0.2594  0.7931  *** 
## 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
W <- solve(V.SCE)
X <- model.matrix(metafor.SCE)
P <- W - W %*% X %*% solve(t(X) %*% W %*% X) %*% t(X) %*% W
c(100 * metafor.SCE$tau2[1] / (metafor.SCE$tau2[1] + (sum(df_main$outcome == "interoception")-1)/sum(diag(P)[df_main$outcome == "interoception"])),
  100 * metafor.SCE$tau2[2] / (metafor.SCE$tau2[2] + (sum(df_main$outcome == "symptoms")-1)/sum(diag(P)[df_main$outcome == "symptoms"])))
## [1] 85.99464 81.24326

Supplementary 3. Additional analyses

A. Using a standard RVE approach

res.S1 <- robumeta::robu(yi ~ outcome - 1, 
                            data = df_main, 
                            studynum = study_ID, 
                            var.eff.size = vi,
                            modelweights = "CORR",
                            small = TRUE,
                            rho = 0.8)$reg_table
res.S1$outcome = gsub("outcome", "", res.S1$labels)

res.S1$Analysis = "Standard RVE approach"

D. Small-study effects

Square root of the eff. sample size

df_main$inv_N = with(df_main, 1/n_exp + 1/n_nexp)
df_main$sqrt_inv_N = sqrt(df_main$inv_N)

sse.1 <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                         mods =  ~ 1 + sqrt_inv_N,
                         data = df_main,
                         random = ~ outcome | study_ID,
                         struct = "DIAG",
                         sparse = TRUE)

res.S4 = coef_sand(model = sse.1, vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.S4[,2:ncol(res.S4)] = round(res.S4[,2:ncol(res.S4)], 3)
res.S4$Analysis = "Small study effects"

kbl(res.S4) %>%
  kable_classic()
outcome beta SE tstat df p_Satt CI_L CI_U Analysis
intrcpt 0.290 0.416 0.695 5.725 0.514 -0.741 1.321 Small study effects
sqrt_inv_N 0.766 1.816 0.422 4.091 0.695 -4.233 5.764 Small study effects

Square root of the eff. sample size + mod

sse.2 <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                         mods =  ~ - 1 + sqrt_inv_N + outcome,
                         data = df_main,
                         random = ~ outcome | study_ID,
                         struct = "DIAG",
                         control=list(optimizer="optim", optmethod="Nelder-Mead"),
                         sparse = TRUE)

res.sse.2 = coef_sand(model = sse.2, vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.sse.2[,2:ncol(res.sse.2)] = round(res.sse.2[,2:ncol(res.sse.2)], 3)

Egger’s test

dat_umb = subset(df_main, select = -c(Author, rob))
names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "es"] = "value"
names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "study_ID"] = "author"
names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "outcome"] = "factor"
names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "n_exp"] = "n_cases"
names(dat_umb)[names(dat_umb) == "n_nexp"] = "n_controls"
dat_umb$year = "2000"
dat_umb$measure = "SMD"
dat_umb$meta_review = "Molteni"
dat_umb$multiple_es = "outcomes"

res_egger = metaumbrella::umbrella(dat_umb, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)

funnel plot symptoms

dat_symptoms = res_egger[[1]]$x
meta::funnel(meta::metagen(TE=value, seTE=se, data=dat_symptoms))

funnel plot interoception

dat_interoception = res_egger[[2]]$x
meta::funnel(meta::metagen(TE=value, seTE=se, data=dat_interoception))
